I've fixed the issue with the left border curves in the SpeedTest component. The problem was that while the main container had the `rounded-3xl` class, the absolutely positioned elements inside it (the Hyperspeed animation background and the gradient overlay) didn't have the same border radius applied.

Changes made:
1. Added `rounded-3xl` class to the Hyperspeed animation container
2. Added `overflow-hidden` to ensure content within that container respects the border radius
3. Added `rounded-3xl` to the gradient overlay as well

These changes ensure that all the layers in your component share the same border-radius, preventing the issue where the curves were suddenly becoming square and disappearing.

The fix works because now all nested absolute elements will maintain the same rounded corners as the parent container, creating a consistent appearance throughout all layers of your component.
