## Summary of Sitemap Styling Implementation

I've implemented two comprehensive solutions to style your sitemap for both search engines and human visitors:

### 1. XSLT Stylesheet for XML Sitemap (Technical Solution)

I created an XSLT stylesheet (`sitemap.xsl`) that transforms your XML sitemap into an attractive, well-organized HTML page when viewed in a browser. This allows:

- **Search engines** to still process the standard XML format
- **Human visitors** to see a beautiful, styled interface with:
 - Category labels and color coding
 - Statistics about your site (total pages, blog posts, high-priority pages)
 - Proper visual hierarchy with responsive design
 - Priority and change frequency indicators with appropriate styling

Key features of this implementation:
- Styled with your brand's primary colors (red and blue)
- Mobile-responsive layout
- Clean, modern interface with proper spacing and typography
- Categorized links with visual indicators
- Interactive hover states for better usability

### 2. Human-Friendly HTML Sitemap Page

I also created a dedicated HTML sitemap page at `/sitemap` with:
- Card-based layout organized by category
- Icon-based navigation for visual appeal
- Responsive grid design for all screen sizes
- Brand-aligned color scheme
- Direct links to all important sections of your site

Key features:
- Beautiful, modern UI with shadow effects and rounded corners
- Organized into logical categories matching your site structure
- Iconography that makes navigation intuitive
- Hover effects for better interactivity
- Link to the XML sitemap for technical users

### Integration with Search Engines

Both solutions are properly integrated with search engines:
1. The XML sitemap references the XSLT stylesheet in its header
2. The robots.txt file has been updated to reference both the XML sitemap and the human-friendly sitemap page
3. The HTML sitemap page includes a link back to the XML version

### Benefits

